<div class="page-article__content-section" id="links">
  <div class="content-section__row">
    <div class="content-section__header">
      <h2 class="title">Links</h2>
      <p class="text--large">What a beautiful day to hit the links.</p>
      <p class="text">This component should be used for navigational purposes or appending items to a list. If you want to move a user from one page to the next or load an overlay, then a link is the right way to go. Avoid using links when asking users to submit final actions. They can be used next to a submit action if want to provide users a way to cancel or close an item, however.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="content-section__row">
    <ul class="guide__list">
      <li class="guide__item">
        <a href="#" class="link--alpha">Link Text</a>
      </li>
      <li class="guide__item">
        <a href="#" class="link--bravo">Link Text</a>
      </li>
      <li class="guide__item">
        <a href="#" class="link--charlie">Link Text</a>
      </li>
      <li class="guide__item">
        <a href="#" class="link--disabled">Link Text</a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="content-section__row">
    <h4 class="content-section__label">Sample Code</h4>
<% code("html") do %>
  <!-- Main Link -->
  <a href="#" class="link--alpha">Link Text</a>

  <!-- Secondary Link -->
  <a href="#" class="link--bravo">Link Text</a>

  <!-- Warning Link -->
  <a href="#" class="link--charlie">Link Text</a>

  <!-- Disabled Link -->
  <a href="#" class="link--disabled">Link Text</a>
<% end %><br/>
  </div>
  <div class="content-section__row">
    <h4 class="content-section__label">HTML Guidelines</h4>
    <p>This table gives you a quick overview of the CSS classes that can be applied to create a link.</p>
    <table class="table">
      <thead class="table__header">
        <th class="table__header-item">Class Name</th>
        <th class="table__header-item">Usage</th>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="table__body">
        <tr>
          <td class="table__body-item" style="width:30%">.link--[type]</td>
          <td class="table__body-item">This should be applied to the element you are styling as a link. The class name should change based on the type of link being used. <% code("html") do %><a href="#" class"link--alpha"></a><% end %></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>